actions.text: Referred to the House Committee on Armed Services.
Mr. Heinrich moved to suspend the rules and pass the bill.
Considered under suspension of the rules.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with forty minutes of debate on H.R. 24.
On motion to suspend the rules and pass the bill Agreed to by voice vote.
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.
Received in the Senate and Read twice and referred to the Committee on Armed Services.

official_title: To redesignate the Department of the Navy as the Department of the Navy and Marine Corps.

summary.text: Redesignates: (1) the Department of the Navy as the Department of the Navy and Marine Corps; and (2) the Secretary of the Navy as the Secretary of the Navy and Marine Corps. Makes similar redesignations with respect to the Department Under Secretary, the Department Assistant Secretaries, and the General Counsel.

titles.title: To redesignate the Department of the Navy as the Department of the Navy and Marine Corps.
